      "titulo": "Secure Communication in VANETs",
      "titulo_en": "Secure Communication in VANETs",
      "enquadramento": "Vehicles communicate in different modes, and exchange information regarding their location, speed, direction among other aspects. Different communication modes are also possible, V2V – Vehicle to Vehicle, V2I – Vehicle to Infrastructure, and V2X – Vehicle to Everything, exchanging messages in a standardized fashion like C-ITS – Cooperative Intelligent Transport Systems.\r\n\r\nDifferent C-ITS standards exist like CAM – Cooperative Awareness Message, DENM - Decentralized Environmental Notification Message, MCM - Manoeuver Coordination Message, which are used with different purposes.\r\n\r\nOne of the biggest issues within C-ITS is the employment of identifiers in the messages which allow tracking vehicles, collect information of routines, among others. Another concern is related with the employment of keys and certificates to encrypt and/or sign the communications using cryptographic solutions that can be vulnerable to quantum computation.  \r\n",
      "objetivos": "The goals related with the identifier’s issues are:\r\n- Validate how a PKI can be established for automotive sector, considering heterogenous vendors, and entities with different infrastructures.\r\n- Validate an approach for pseudonyms/and or similar approach like butterfly keys in VANETs.\r\n- Design, develop a proof of concept (PoC) in VANETS.\r\n- Evaluation of the proof of concept (PoC).\r\n\r\nThe goals related with the cryptographic issues are:\r\n- Validate an approach quantum-safe cryptographic protocols in VANETs.\r\n- Design, develop a proof of concept (PoC) in VANETS.\r\n- Evaluation of the proof of concept (PoC).\r\n\r\nAdditionally, the results can be published in a scientific publication.\r\n",
      "plano1": "T1.1 – Analysis of the State of the art in VANETs and related issue.\r\nT1.2 – Design the architecture for the intended solution.\r\nT1.3 – Preliminary validation though simplistic scenario using Vanetza-NAP project (https://github.com/ADSafeVANET/vanetza-nap-adsafe)\r\nT1.4 – Write the intermediary report.\r\n\r\n",
      "plano2": "T2.1 – Implementation of intended solution.\r\nT2.2 – Benchmarking of the solution, considering more complex and realistic scenarios.\r\nT2.3 – Write the final report and scientific publication.\r\n",
