      "titulo": "Integração Assistida por IA e Geração de Fluxos de Trabalho",
      "titulo_en": "AI-Assisted Integration and Workflow Generation ",
      "enquadramento": "Intermedia already has an integration platform that enables systems, applications and product capabilities to connect through APIs, events, connectors and workflow automation. As the number of customer use cases grows, creating integrations and workflows can become dependent on specialized technical knowledge, engineering availability and manual configuration. \r\n\r\nThis internship will research how Artificial Intelligence and natural language interfaces can democratize the creation of integrations and workflows. The goal is not to replace the existing integration platform, but to experiment with mechanisms that allow users, solution engineers, product teams or partners to describe an integration need in natural language and receive a validated workflow, connector configuration, API mapping or integration blueprint that can be reviewed, tested and deployed safely. \r\n\r\nThe work will explore how Large Language Models, workflow planning, API discovery, schema mapping, policy validation and human-in-the-loop approval can simplify integration development while preserving security, reliability and governance requirements. \r\n\r\n\r\nInnovation aspects:\r\n- Democratization of integration and workflow creation by allowing users to describe business needs in natural language \r\n- AI-assisted generation of structured workflow definitions, connector configurations, API mappings and integration blueprints \r\n- Use of platform metadata, API specifications, schemas and connector catalogs as context for reliable workflow generation \r\n- Combination of LLM-based planning with deterministic validation to reduce hallucinations and unsafe integrations \r\n- Human-in-the-loop review and approval flow to ensure generated workflows are explainable, testable and governed before activation \r\n- Automatic schema mapping and parameter extraction to reduce manual configuration effort \r\n- Evaluation of productivity gains, correctness and safety compared with traditional manual integration development \r\n- Practical productization guidance for embedding AI capabilities into an existing enterprise integration platform ",
      "objetivos": "- Research approaches for generating integrations and workflows from natural language descriptions \r\n- Design and prototype an AI-assisted mechanism that converts user intent into workflow definitions, API calls, mappings or integration blueprints \r\n- Explore how the existing Intermedia integration platform can expose metadata, connectors, schemas and policies to AI-assisted workflow generation \r\n- Implement validation mechanisms to detect missing information, unsafe actions, incompatible schemas and policy violations \r\n- Prototype a human-in-the-loop review flow where generated integrations can be inspected, corrected, tested and approved before execution \r\n- Evaluate usability, correctness, safety, latency and productivity gains of AI-assisted integration creation ",
      "plano1": "- Onboard to the Intermedia integration platform, available connectors, APIs, workflow concepts and governance requirements \r\n- Study current integration creation flows and identify friction points where AI could reduce complexity or manual effort \r\n- Research natural language to workflow generation, LLM function calling, API planning, schema matching, tool use and workflow orchestration techniques \r\n- Define representative use cases, such as CRM synchronization, contact center event routing, ticket creation, notification workflows, analytics export and customer data enrichment \r\n- Design a target architecture for AI-assisted integration generation, including prompt orchestration, platform metadata retrieval, workflow generation and validation services \r\n- Create a controlled catalog of sample APIs, connectors, schemas and workflow templates for experimentation \r\n- Prototype the first version of a natural language interface that generates structured workflow definitions or integration blueprints ",
      "plano2": "- Extend the prototype to support schema mapping, parameter extraction, connector selection and multi-step workflow generation \r\n- Implement validation rules for security, permissions, data handling, required fields, execution constraints and platform compatibility \r\n- Add explainability features so users can understand why a workflow was generated and what each step does \r\n- Prototype a review, test and approval flow where a generated integration can be simulated before being activated \r\n- Run experiments comparing manual integration creation with AI-assisted generation across selected use cases \r\n- Evaluate generated workflows using metrics such as correctness, completeness, safety, user effort reduction and time-to-first-working-integration \r\n- Deliver final presentation and documentation with architecture, prototype results, limitations and recommendations for productization ",
      "sugestao_juri": null,
      "tem_juri": false,
      "add_aluno_pos_inicio_candidatura": false,
      "inicio_candidaturas": false,
      "condicoes": "- You will be integrated into a Product Area team, working closely with engineers and stakeholders, which will allow you to gain practical experience within a real product environment. Throughout the internship, you will also be invited to participate in training sessions and other company activities. Whenever relevant, you may also have the opportunity to interact with more senior profiles and leadership, gaining a broader understanding of the company and the business.\r\n- The internship follows a hybrid work model, with interns expected to work from the office 2–3 days per week. A PC or Mac will also be provided for the duration of the internship.\r\n- At the end of the internship, subject to a positive evaluation and depending on the company’s needs, there may be the possibility of continuing your journey at Intermedia.\r\n- The internship includes a monthly scholarship of €900, subject to positive performance evaluation.",
      "observacoes": "You may not yet have had contact with Intermedia (https://www.intermedia.com/), so in addition to discussing the internship conditions, we would also like to tell you a little bit about who we are.\r\n\r\nIntermedia is an international technology company with more than 30 years of experience, developing cloud communication solutions and placing people, collaboration, and innovation at the center of its culture. Although our presence in Portugal is relatively recent (since 2023), the company has been growing very consistently and already has more than 200 employees in Portugal, several of whom have an academic background from DEI.\r\n\r\nAt Intermedia, we believe that learning by doing, sharing knowledge, and working as a team are essential for both technical and personal growth. To support you throughout your journey, you will have both a mentor and a supervisor who will closely guide and support you during the internship.\r\n",
