      "titulo": "Redes Neuronais por Impulsos: um caminho para soluções de aprendizagem computacional mais sustentáveis",
      "titulo_en": "Spiking Neural Networks: a way forward to more sustainable machine learning solutions",
      "enquadramento": "Recent years have been highly prolific in Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Machine Learning advancements, culminating in increasingly powerful and complex solutions. Artificial Neural Networks (ANNs) represent the pinnacle of this paradigm, serving as the most critical pillar of AI's widespread success. Yet, despite their ubiquity across a wide range of domains, such solutions are also highly demanding in terms of data, energy, and computational resources. By closely mimicking the real mechanisms of biological neurons, Spiking Neural Networks (SNNs) promise to improve energy and computational efficiency, especially when implemented on neuromorphic hardware. ",
      "objetivos": "The objective of this internship is twofold: first, to conduct a thorough literature review on SNNs, as well as to explore the currently available libraries/frameworks implementing such models; second, through an empirical setting, study and compare the energy-saving gains of SNNs in comparison with the traditional and comparable ANNs. The internship should provide the candidate with greater awareness of energy-saving and sustainability issues in modern AI solutions.",
      "plano1": "1. State of the art review \r\n2. Review and ranking of libraries and frameworks delivering implementations of SNNs.\r\n3. Draft an experimental setting (methodology, models, tools, data sets, performance metrics, etc.) for supporting the future empirical study comparing SNNs against traditional ANNs, focusing on energy-efficiency outcomes. It should also consider the use of neuromorphic hardware.\r\n4. Writing of the intermediate internship report.",
      "plano2": "5. Review and execute the final experimental setting.\r\n6. Explore, analyze, and discuss the results from an energy-saving and sustainable point of view, and analyze the real-world gains of deploying SNNs to neuromorphic hardware.\r\n7. Preparation of a paper for a conference or journal (to be determined).\r\n8. Writing and submission of the thesis.",
      "sugestao_juri": null,
      "tem_juri": false,
      "add_aluno_pos_inicio_candidatura": false,
      "inicio_candidaturas": false,
      "condicoes": "The internship will take place at the Laboratory of Artificial Neural Networks (LARN-CISUC) with regular meetings with the supervision team. The candidate should be highly motivated to conduct research in artificial intelligence, machine learning, and data science. Experience with Python, ANNs, and Deep Learning is essential, as well as with related machine learning algorithms and software/programming tools. In addition to the laboratory itself, the selected candidate will be integrated into the research team currently working on these issues, namely, Professors Francisco Antunes and Bernardete Ribeiro.",
      "observacoes": "A research grant opportunity may become available during the internship, depending on the student’s performance.",
